# Chess Game in Java

Welcome to my Java Console Chess Game! This project is a simple yet robust implementation of the classic chess game, designed to be played in the console or terminal. It is developed entirely in Java, showcasing object-oriented programming principles and providing an interactive gameplay experience.

## Features

- **Complete Chess Rules**: Implements all the standard chess rules including castling, pawn promotion, and en-passant.
- **Player vs Player**: Allows two players to compete against each other on the same machine.
- **Console-Based UI**: Simple and clean user interface using console output for easy gameplay.
- **Move Validation**: Automatically checks for valid moves and keeps track of the game status.
